text: The Dassault-Breguet/Dornier Alpha Jet is a French and German training aircraft. Its first flight was in October 1973. It is a twin-turbojet, two- seat aircraft. It is used by the Patrouille de France, the air show team of the French Air Force. Category:French military aircraft Category:German military aircraft
title: Dassault/Dornier Alpha Jet
